Calling song. Along Mager Road, callings of numerous specimens were first heard at around 1930 hours and last heard at around 2000 hours (both in December and May). Calling song is a loud resonant hum emitting from within a shallow burrow. Pitch is low (frequency = about 1.5 kHz) and pulse rate consistent of 140 s - 1 (
Fig. 4
).
